Edition:
Quote:  [Facsimile letter from Maori Girl of 16 in 1892, in `pidgin', ending:] My sister say you fond of little boys and girls well py gorry bimeby I give you plenty /I send you xx/ Hohepa.
Notes:  [1892] 1924 Gibson Gibbie Galoot

Date:  0/0/1956
Source:  NZ Fishes: An Identification Guide
Author:  GRAHAM
Vol / Page:  355
Edition:
Quote:  When both parties had collected their fish the fishermen, for a joke, would say to the Maoris: `Got many Pigfish today, Ehoa? Let's have a look!' and on examining the kits a Flounder here and there would be seen in with the Pigfish; but the Maori women were not to be out-done and would exclaim with great vehemence: `By gorry, Mister, I never seen him go in, he must have jumped in when I not looking!'
